.TH F00-WC 1 "2026" "f00 0.15.11" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
f00\-wc \- print newline, word, and byte counts (f00tils)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B f00\-wc
[\fIOPTION\fR]... [\fIFILE\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Print newline, word, and byte counts for each FILE, and a total line if
more than one FILE is specified. With no FILE, or when FILE is \-,
read standard input. Pure assembly multicall. MIT.
.PP
Default is modern mode.
.B \-\-core
selects strict GNU wc\-compatible output.
.SH COREUTILS FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-bytes\fR
print the byte counts
.TP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-chars\fR
print the character counts
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-lines\fR
print the newline counts
.TP
\fB\-w\fR, \fB\-\-words\fR
print the word counts
.TP
\fB\-L\fR, \fB\-\-max\-line\-length\fR
print the maximum display width
.PP
See
.B f00\-wc \-\-help
for the full flag list.
.SH MODERN FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-\-core\fR
strict coreutils\-compatible output
.TP
\fB\-j\fR, \fB\-\-json\fR
JSON counts
.TP
\fB\-\-csv\fR
CSV counts
.SH AUTHOR
f00 contributors. License MIT.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR wc (1),
.BR f00 (1)
.PP
https://f00.sh
